git fetch vs git merge vs git pull vs git rebase
-------------------------------------------------------
git pull : git fetch + git merge

git fetch : downloads the change from main 
git fetch origin 

git merge : integrates into local repo


		1. main A --- B --- X 
		
			feature A --- B --- C — D
			
			git checkout feature
			git fetch origin
			git merge origin/main
			
			        C --- D
			       /       \
			A --- B         M. - new merge commit
			       \       /
			        X -----
		
		
		2. main  A --- B --- C --- F --- G
		           \
				feature     D --- E
				
				git checkout feature
				git fetch origin
				git merge origin/main

			Keeps history


git rebase : A --- B --- C --- F --- G
		           \             \
		            D --- E ------ M  - new merge commit

			git checkout feature
			git rebase main feature

			A --- B --- C --- F --- G --- D' --- E'
			
			Rewrites commit history
			feature branch commits are put into main - each commit in feature is a commit in main	
			The golden rule of rebasing :: only use if no one else is working on the main branch - NEVER USE



